ረደልጁም\" was split into \"ወረደ\" and \"ልጁም\"; \"ወረደተማሪዎች\" into \"ወረደ\" and \"ተማሪዎች\"; and \"ወረፋድንበሩ\" into \"ወረፋ\" and \"ድንበሩ\". Suffixes like 'ም' and 'ና' were kept attached to their preceding words when they did not form standalone valid words.\n\n**Protocol 2: The Judge (Nonsense Removal)**\nSeveral strings were discarded due to being unfixable gibberish or non-Amharic noise: \"ወራካላ\", \"ወራውሬ\", \"ወሬዛ\" (unfixable gibberish), and \"ወርሺፕ\" (non-Amharic transliteration of 'worship').\n\n**Protocol 3: The Corrector (Visual Repair)**\nCommon OCR errors were corrected based on linguistic context: \"ወራሃዊ\" was corrected to \"ወርሃዊ\", \"ወራሸ\" to \"ወራሽ\", and \"ወራተ\" to \"ወራት\".\n\n**Protocol 4: The Lemmatizer (Global Citation Form)**\nFor every valid word, its base dictionary entry (infinitive or root noun) was identified. Examples include \"መወርወር\" for \"ወረወረውም\", \"መውረድ\" for \"ወረደላቸው\", and \"ወረዳ\" for \"ወረዳዎቹን\".\n\n**Protocol 5: The Translator (Nuance Expansion)**\nComprehensive English synonyms were provided to capture the full breadth of each word's meaning.\n\n**Protocol 6: The Grammarian (Linguistic Tagging)**\nEach word was assigned its appropriate Part of Speech (e.g., Noun, Verb, Adjective).\n\n**Protocol 7: The Filter (Size Constraint)**\nAll included words and roots consist of at least two characters, adhering to the size constraint.\n\n**Protocol 8: Executive Summary (Scholarly Guesses)**\nA notable scholarly guess was made for \"ወርምን\". Given its ambiguous nature, it was interpreted and corrected as an OCR error for \"ወርቅን\" (gold, accusative), as this represented the most plausible single-word Amharic correction, maintaining a single entry for the original string's intent.","input_words":["ወረከት","ወረወረውም","ወረወሩአትም","ወረደላቸው","ወረደልጁም","ወረደተማሪዎች","ወረዳዎቹን","ወረዳዎቻችን","ወረድሽና","ወረፋድንበሩ","ወራሃዊ","ወራሪንና","ወራራውን","ወራሸ","ወራሾችንም","ወራተ","ወራትዋ","ወራካላ","ወራውሬ","ወራዳም","ወሬህንም","ወሬአችንን","ወሬዛ","ወርምን","ወርረውታልና","ወርሰዋታል","ወርሶሃል","ወርሺፕ","ወርቀዘቦውን","ወርቃችሁም"],"batch_number":null,"bat